{"term":"1963","caseName":"Mercer v. Theriot","caseLink":"https://www.oyez.org/cases/1963/336","caseTranscripts":[{"transcriptTitle":"Oral Argument - April 22, 1964 (Part 1)","transcriptLink":"https://apps.oyez.org/player/#/warren11/oral_argument_audio/13984","transcript":[{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"Number 336, Wanda Mercer versus Paris Theriot.","start":0,"stop":26.396,"duration":26.4},{"text":"Mr. Brumfield.","start":26.396,"stop":27.388,"duration":0.99}]},{"speakerName":"H. Alva Brumfield","textObjs":[{"text":"Yes, sir.","start":27.388,"stop":28.023,"duration":0.63},{"text":"Mr. Chief Justice and may it please the Court.","start":28.023,"stop":35.725,"duration":7.7},{"text":"This is a death action brought by a widow for the death of her husband who was killed on Grand Isle which is on the shoreline of the State of Louisiana, the action being brought under Article 2315 of our Civil Code which is our death action statute.","start":35.725,"stop":59.766,"duration":24.04},{"text":"It was brought in the federal court on the ground of diversity of citizenship as the widower is a citizen of the State of Texas.","start":59.766,"stop":70.859,"duration":11.09},{"text":"A jury trial was held and the jury rendered a verdict in favor of the widow.","start":70.859,"stop":80.356,"duration":9.5},{"text":"The facts of this case briefly stated, the deceased, (Inaudible) Mercer was an offshore worker, working out in the Gulf of Mexico and he lived in a trailer on Grand Isle and he go to and from his work out in the Gulf by boat.","start":80.356,"stop":103.513,"duration":23.16},{"text":"He came in, docked on Grand Isle -- that docked there on December the 18th, 1955 at approximately 7 o'clock of that evening.","start":103.513,"stop":115.338,"duration":11.82},{"text":"As a rule, he would ride with coworkers who drop him off with his trailer where he lived with his wife.","start":115.338,"stop":122.503,"duration":7.17},{"text":"But on this night, he decided to not ride with his coworkers and he would walk home, it's about four miles to the East.","start":122.503,"stop":132.4,"duration":9.9},{"text":"There's only one road on Grand Isle being Highway 1.","start":132.4,"stop":137.024,"duration":4.62},{"text":"He was found on the right hand side of the road on the shoulder of the road the next morning, 6:00 or 6:30 am, faced down some two or three feet from the asphalt portion of the highway on the shoulder of the road, dead.","start":137.024,"stop":156.212,"duration":19.19},{"text":"There were tire marks showing that on the shoulder of the road, at and near his body, a -- a pool of blood in the tire mark on the shoulder of the road and he was severely injured, his legs were broken, liver, spleen ruptured, spine chord injury, skull fracture, brain damage resulting in his death as shown by the coroner's report.","start":156.212,"stop":189.565,"duration":33.35},{"text":"There were no eyewitnesses to this accident that caused his death.He wore a -- a denim overalls of blue.","start":189.565,"stop":204.984,"duration":15.42},{"text":"The -- when he -- when his body was found, the investigative officers were notified and they came to the scene and made some pictures of the body there on the shoulder of the road which pictures are introduced into evidence and are before the Court here.","start":204.984,"stop":225.784,"duration":20.8},{"text":"The officers also made an -- an investigation and determined that there was a man that had been on the island as they would call it down there, in a bar, a fisherman's bar wharf and drinking scotch and water all afternoon.","start":225.784,"stop":245.135,"duration":19.35},{"text":"This man was Paris Theriot and he owned an automobile agency and he came down there to sell, the owner of the business there, an automobile which he did consummate the sale that afternoon, drinking scotch and whiskey during the course of the afternoon.","start":245.135,"stop":265.066,"duration":19.93},{"text":"And he left the bar at about 7:30 of that night, 7 pm.","start":265.066,"stop":274.547,"duration":9.48},{"text":"It was foggy and rainy, drizzly evening.","start":274.547,"stop":280.442,"duration":5.89},{"text":"Immediately, the officers -- he became the suspect and the officers went to his -- where he lived, he got a home on Grand Isle as well as in Golden Meadow, Louisiana.","start":280.442,"stop":293.341,"duration":12.9},{"text":"And they went up to Golden Meadow and found him and asked him if he'd been on the island and he first denied that he hadn't -- hadn't been there at all but then he later admitted that he had been there.","start":293.341,"stop":305.409,"duration":12.07},{"text":"And they asked him where his car was and he pointed out to it across the bar there.","start":305.409,"stop":312.211,"duration":6.8},{"text":"And the officers got the car and made some pictures of it in an investigation, examination of the automobile and found that the right rim of the headlight was missing.","start":312.211,"stop":324.733,"duration":12.52},{"text":"That the front fender was dented on the front and that there was a dent on the hood of the automobile, about near the windshield and that in this denture -- indentations on the automobile, there was a blue coloring.","start":324.733,"stop":342.941,"duration":18.21},{"text":"And so the officers took scrapings of this coloring which was fabric-like and matched according to the testimony of the officials, the -- the denim overalls that this deceased was wearing.","start":342.941,"stop":357.465,"duration":14.52},{"text":"Mr. Theriot was then asked if he had washed his car and he denied that he had, although he --- he said that it always been washed every morning but this morning, it hadn't been washed.","start":357.465,"stop":370.136,"duration":12.67},{"text":"Yet the officers found some powdery -- powdery substance, one of them described, it looked like Old Dutch Cleanser on the automobile indicating that it had been washed.","start":370.136,"stop":381.775,"duration":11.64},{"text":"The officers also found a towel -- stuff behind the seat cover behind the back -- the front seat up between the seat and the seat cover of a brown substance which appeared like blood.","start":381.775,"stop":395.136,"duration":13.36},{"text":"They put the car on a rack and found underneath the car some hairy substance and -- and blood under the steering mechanism, underneath the car.","start":395.136,"stop":404.859,"duration":9.72},{"text":"Putting all of those bits of evidence and envelops for marking, they took it to the courthouse of Jefferson Parish for it to be taken to the laboratory for testing.","start":404.859,"stop":421.522,"duration":16.66},{"text":"All of these evidence disappeared.","start":421.522,"stop":424.417,"duration":2.89},{"text":"The only thing that remained was these photographs that were made by the investigating officers showing the deceased and the car itself.","start":424.417,"stop":440.746,"duration":16.33},{"text":"Faced with this evidence as to the damage to his automobile, confronted with that, he was asked by these officers.\"","start":440.746,"stop":451.427,"duration":10.68},{"text":"Well, how did that happen?\"","start":451.427,"stop":456.722,"duration":5.29},{"text":"His answer to them was, \"Well, I hit a cow.\"","start":456.722,"stop":461.36,"duration":4.64},{"text":"And then they kept pressing him about that and then he changed the story and said, \"No, I ran into a truck before I went down to Grand Isle, I was going along the road and ran into rear of a stake body truck.","start":461.36,"stop":475.112,"duration":13.75},{"text":"And I damaged my car that way and a piece of wood fell out of the truck and hit my car and I ran off the road but I came back on the road.\"","start":475.112,"stop":485.937,"duration":10.82},{"text":"So the officers took him out there to the scene where he said he had this wreck before he went to Grand Isle and asked him to point out where it was.","start":485.937,"stop":495.98,"duration":10.04},{"text":"And the officers testified that if he had -- there's no marking there at all of showing a car going off the road.","start":495.98,"stop":503.024,"duration":7.04},{"text":"He -- he estimated 100 -- a 150 feet, he went off the road but there's no tire marks at all showing that the car had -- any card had gone of the road.","start":503.024,"stop":512.105,"duration":9.08},{"text":"And had there been a car that -- going off the road at that point, it was so soggy and mud -- muddy that the car couldn't have gotten out itself and it would have been pulled out.","start":512.105,"stop":522.506,"duration":10.4},{"text":"But yet, he stuck to that story.","start":522.506,"stop":525.097,"duration":2.59}]},{"speakerName":"Potter Stewart","textObjs":[{"text":"His story was that he had had this -- this had happened on his way from Golden Meadow after Grand Isle, back there?","start":525.097,"stop":529.951,"duration":4.85}]},{"speakerName":"H. Alva Brumfield","textObjs":[{"text":"No.","start":529.951,"stop":530.363,"duration":0.41},{"text":"It happened on -- on the way up to the bar before he started down to the Grand Isle, it -- around noon that Sunday.","start":530.363,"stop":537.011,"duration":6.65}]},{"speakerName":"Potter Stewart","textObjs":[{"text":"That Sunday, that same day.","start":537.011,"stop":538.056,"duration":1.05}]},{"speakerName":"H. Alva Brumfield","textObjs":[{"text":"Yes.","start":538.056,"stop":538.512,"duration":0.46}]},{"speakerName":"Potter Stewart","textObjs":[{"text":"But --","start":538.512,"stop":539.605,"duration":1.09}]},{"speakerName":"H. Alva Brumfield","textObjs":[{"text":"It wouldn't -- and then he went on to Grand Isle after he had this -- bumped into the back end of this truck.","start":539.605,"stop":546.675,"duration":7.07}]},{"speakerName":"Potter Stewart","textObjs":[{"text":"That was his story before (Inaudible) --","start":546.675,"stop":547.712,"duration":1.04}]},{"speakerName":"H. Alva Brumfield","textObjs":[{"text":"Yes.","start":547.712,"stop":548.219,"duration":0.51}]},{"speakerName":"Potter Stewart","textObjs":[{"text":"-- on -- on his -- and -- and then later, he went over to Grand Isle to --","start":548.219,"stop":552.358,"duration":4.14}]},{"speakerName":"H. Alva Brumfield","textObjs":[{"text":"To sell this automo --","start":552.358,"stop":553.274,"duration":0.92}]},{"speakerName":"Potter Stewart","textObjs":[{"text":"(voice overlap) about selling the automobile.","start":553.274,"stop":555.143,"duration":1.87}]},{"speakerName":"H. Alva Brumfield","textObjs":[{"text":"That's right, sir.","start":555.143,"stop":558.756,"duration":3.61},{"text":"But on this -- on the trial of this case, the -- the demeanor, the alibis, the change of story of this -- of this suspect, of this defendant is all important in this case and -- and was a determinant factor of the jury reaching the decision that it did in my opinion.","start":558.756,"stop":580.862,"duration":22.11},{"text":"An additional factor, this man sold his business, interest in -- in his partnership of this automobile agency to his brother.","start":580.862,"stop":592.565,"duration":11.7},{"text":"About seven days after this -- Mercer, the deceased here was found.","start":592.565,"stop":599.354,"duration":6.79}]},{"speakerName":"Potter Stewart","textObjs":[{"text":"Was it brought before the jury that some of his evidence had disappeared that they've been collected by the officers?","start":599.354,"stop":604.354,"duration":5}]},{"speakerName":"H. Alva Brumfield","textObjs":[{"text":"It was all -- of course it was brought before the -- for the jury by the -- all of the officers were put on the stand and they were asked, \"Where was this evidence?","start":604.354,"stop":612.771,"duration":8.42},{"text":"Here we can resolve this thing without any question at all.\"","start":612.771,"stop":616.165,"duration":3.39},{"text":"And -- and they all testified, of course that it -- that it had disappeared.","start":616.165,"stop":620.348,"duration":4.18},{"text":"They didn't know what happened to it.","start":620.348,"stop":622.631,"duration":2.28},{"text":"And the -- and the -- one of the state of -- officers who investigated this was asked a question on cross examination that was there, a payoff and he stated that he heard that there was.","start":622.631,"stop":634.531,"duration":11.9}]},{"speakerName":"Potter Stewart","textObjs":[{"text":"Who -- who asked that question, defence counsel?","start":634.531,"stop":636.882,"duration":2.35}]},{"speakerName":"H. Alva Brumfield","textObjs":[{"text":"No, I asked that question --","start":636.882,"stop":637.423,"duration":0.54}]},{"speakerName":"Potter Stewart","textObjs":[{"text":"You asked (Voice Overlap).","start":637.423,"stop":637.906,"duration":0.48}]},{"speakerName":"H. Alva Brumfield","textObjs":[{"text":"-- on direct examination, I mean on cross examination without any objection and the -- and the attorney representing the defendant who is not Mr. Loeb here --","start":637.906,"stop":648.427,"duration":10.52}]},{"speakerName":"Potter Stewart","textObjs":[{"text":"Yes.","start":648.427,"stop":649.278,"duration":0.85}]},{"speakerName":"H. Alva Brumfield","textObjs":[{"text":"-- didn't -- went into it farther on these questions of payoff.","start":649.278,"stop":653.885,"duration":4.61},{"text":"And it was just generally rumored that there had been a payoff and the rim never did show up.","start":653.885,"stop":659.136,"duration":5.25},{"text":"And I -- I'll -- I'll go into that a little later with regard to the mandate, try to carry out the mandate of the Fifth Circuit Court of Appeal after the case went up to the Fifth Circuit.","start":659.136,"stop":670.352,"duration":11.22}]},{"speakerName":"Potter Stewart","textObjs":[{"text":"Except for the general rumor of a payoff that was testified to?","start":670.352,"stop":675.602,"duration":5.25},{"text":"And except for the testimony that the evidence had disappeared, was there anything more specific as to how or where or to whom it had been -- the evidence had disappeared?","start":675.602,"stop":685.821,"duration":10.22}]},{"speakerName":"H. Alva Brumfield","textObjs":[{"text":"Well, Judge, I took the -- the depositions of all -- all of these officials over again, even after the trial.","start":685.821,"stop":695.044,"duration":9.22},{"text":"And one officer would -- would say, \"I heard that (Inaudible) was paid $10,000 to hide this rim and destroy the evidence.\"","start":695.044,"stop":705.73,"duration":10.69},{"text":"And then take the -- (Inaudible) deposition, he would deny it and say, \"No, I heard that the Officer Dolph (Inaudible) got the $10,000.\"","start":705.73,"stop":712.439,"duration":6.71},{"text":"So it was just one to the other, accusing each other of getting the $10,000 but all denying it.","start":712.439,"stop":719.445,"duration":7.01},{"text":"And -- and that was what we were --","start":719.445,"stop":721.207,"duration":1.76}]},{"speakerName":"Potter Stewart","textObjs":[{"text":"All agreeing that there had been evidence which had disappeared.","start":721.207,"stop":724.059,"duration":2.85}]},{"speakerName":"H. Alva Brumfield","textObjs":[{"text":"All agreeing.","start":724.059,"stop":724.855,"duration":0.8},{"text":"There's no question about that.","start":724.855,"stop":726.47,"duration":1.62},{"text":"The -- they all agreed that the evidence was gathered and it had -- and it all disappeared.","start":726.47,"stop":732.345,"duration":5.88},{"text":"And the only -- and the reason as I say that the pictures didn't disappear because an officer had the negatives in his home.","start":732.345,"stop":739.637,"duration":7.29},{"text":"And I found out about the pictures and got copies of the prints made from these negatives which prints are in the evidence here before -- before the Court.","start":739.637,"stop":750.239,"duration":10.6},{"text":"And -- and with -- with that, the circumstances, as I've outlined generally here, the jury rendered a verdict for the plaintiff.","start":750.239,"stop":762.303,"duration":12.06}]},{"speakerName":"Arthur J. Goldberg","textObjs":[{"text":"(Inaudible)","start":762.303,"stop":762.745,"duration":0.44}]},{"speakerName":"H. Alva Brumfield","textObjs":[{"text":"Yes.","start":762.745,"stop":763.001,"duration":0.26}]},{"speakerName":"Arthur J. Goldberg","textObjs":[{"text":"(Inaudible)","start":763.001,"stop":763.618,"duration":0.62}]},{"speakerName":"H. Alva Brumfield","textObjs":[{"text":"Yes.","start":763.618,"stop":764.748,"duration":1.13}]},{"speakerName":"Arthur J. Goldberg","textObjs":[{"text":"(Inaudible)","start":764.748,"stop":771.712,"duration":6.96}]},{"speakerName":"H. Alva Brumfield","textObjs":[{"text":"No it didn't, Judge -- Mr. Justice Goldberg, the -- our basic tort law is in one article of the Civil Code, Article 2315 which uses the word \"fault\" -- he -- to cause it by damage by fault but is synonymous with the Court's inter -- that is being negligence.","start":771.712,"stop":791.88,"duration":20.17},{"text":"And the -- and the general principles of negligence of the law is the same in Louisiana as all the rest of the states.Of course, we come -- we base it on our Napoleonic code but it -- rather than the common law.","start":791.88,"stop":802.663,"duration":10.78}]},{"speakerName":"Arthur J. Goldberg","textObjs":[{"text":"(Inaudible)","start":802.663,"stop":806.559,"duration":3.9}]},{"speakerName":"H. Alva Brumfield","textObjs":[{"text":"No, by preponderance of the evidence, the proximate cause, all of those terms, we have the same there.","start":806.559,"stop":813.917,"duration":7.36},{"text":"We have a comparative negligence in our code but the -- the courts have adopted the common law rule and of -- of contributory negligence rather than comparative negligence.","start":813.917,"stop":825.389,"duration":11.47},{"text":"Other than that, we are pretty well in line, the only -- the only difference we have with regard to trying negligence cases down in Louisiana is we don't have a infective civil jury trial in our state because the appellate court can do what the Fifth Circuit Court did here and that was, make its own determinations of fact and substitute its determination of fact for that of the jury.","start":825.389,"stop":852.768,"duration":27.38},{"text":"And that's the reason wherein we have the diversity of citizenship.","start":852.768,"stop":856.041,"duration":3.27},{"text":"We bring our cases in the federal court in order to get an effective jury trial.","start":856.041,"stop":861.335,"duration":5.29}]},{"speakerName":"Potter Stewart","textObjs":[{"text":"Its --","start":861.335,"stop":861.468,"duration":0.13}]},{"speakerName":"H. Alva Brumfield","textObjs":[{"text":"But --","start":861.468,"stop":861.745,"duration":0.28}]},{"speakerName":"Potter Stewart","textObjs":[{"text":"Excuse me.","start":861.745,"stop":862.177,"duration":0.43}]},{"speakerName":"H. Alva Brumfield","textObjs":[{"text":"Yes.","start":862.177,"stop":862.546,"duration":0.37}]},{"speakerName":"Potter Stewart","textObjs":[{"text":"Go ahead.","start":862.546,"stop":863.973,"duration":1.43},{"text":"It --","start":863.973,"stop":864.103,"duration":0.13}]},{"speakerName":"H. Alva Brumfield","textObjs":[{"text":"Where the only state in the union that allows that.","start":864.103,"stop":866.76,"duration":2.66}]},{"speakerName":"Potter Stewart","textObjs":[{"text":"Which allows what?","start":866.76,"stop":868.132,"duration":1.37}]},{"speakerName":"H. Alva Brumfield","textObjs":[{"text":"The -- the appellate court to substitute its own findings of fact for that of the --","start":868.132,"stop":871.327,"duration":3.2}]},{"speakerName":"Potter Stewart","textObjs":[{"text":"It -- it's in effect the trial de novo of the facts.","start":871.327,"stop":873.235,"duration":1.91}]},{"speakerName":"H. Alva Brumfield","textObjs":[{"text":"It's the trial de novo on appeal, yes.","start":873.235,"stop":874.615,"duration":1.38}]},{"speakerName":"Potter Stewart","textObjs":[{"text":"In your state system.","start":874.615,"stop":875.612,"duration":1}]},{"speakerName":"H. Alva Brumfield","textObjs":[{"text":"Yes sir.","start":875.612,"stop":875.952,"duration":0.34}]},{"speakerName":"Potter Stewart","textObjs":[{"text":"But you don't get it, do you?","start":875.952,"stop":877.873,"duration":1.92},{"text":"Going to the -- and the reason you -- you've -- if you have diversity of citizenship that a plaintiff will go on to the federal court as to avoid that in the federal system.","start":877.873,"stop":886.829,"duration":8.96}]},{"speakerName":"H. Alva Brumfield","textObjs":[{"text":"That's exactly right and that's the reason I brought it here.","start":886.829,"stop":889.743,"duration":2.91},{"text":"But then I was faced with the -- this reversal in the -- by the Fifth Circuit with a -- with a mandate that is unparalleled.","start":889.743,"stop":899.199,"duration":9.46},{"text":"I haven't been able to find any precedent for the type of mandate that was attached to the remand and reversal in this case in the -- in the entire jurisprudence of this Court or any other state.","start":899.199,"stop":913.191,"duration":13.99}]},{"speakerName":"Tom C. Clark","textObjs":[{"text":"Well, do I understand it correctly that Louisiana law (Inaudible)?","start":913.191,"stop":918.948,"duration":5.76}]},{"speakerName":"H. Alva Brumfield","textObjs":[{"text":"Well, we have the framework for it.","start":918.948,"stop":920.715,"duration":1.77},{"text":"The procedure for it was there are few, the jury trials in the state court in civil matters.","start":920.715,"stop":926.334,"duration":5.62},{"text":"And many of the jurisdictions -- I've tried the first jury trial for -- in a civil matter that's ever been tried in the history of the -- the whole district.","start":926.334,"stop":935.343,"duration":9.01}]},{"speakerName":"Arthur J. Goldberg","textObjs":[{"text":"(Inaudible)","start":935.343,"stop":945.855,"duration":10.51}]},{"speakerName":"H. Alva Brumfield","textObjs":[{"text":"No, they just -- they just -- make its own finding --","start":945.855,"stop":948.945,"duration":3.09}]},{"speakerName":"Arthur J. Goldberg","textObjs":[{"text":"(Inaudible)","start":948.945,"stop":949.163,"duration":0.22}]},{"speakerName":"H. Alva Brumfield","textObjs":[{"text":"From the Cole record.","start":949.163,"stop":950.926,"duration":1.76},{"text":"And that's the reason you have so few jury trials in the state court in Louisiana.","start":950.926,"stop":954.888,"duration":3.96}]},{"speakerName":"UNKNOWN","textObjs":[{"text":"(Inaudible)","start":954.888,"stop":956.204,"duration":1.32}]},{"speakerName":"H. Alva Brumfield","textObjs":[{"text":"I brought it in -- in the forum of the federal jurisdiction in order to get an effective jury trial.","start":956.204,"stop":963.126,"duration":6.92}]},{"speakerName":"Potter Stewart","textObjs":[{"text":"And this is the --","start":963.126,"stop":963.184,"duration":0.06}]},{"speakerName":"Tom C. Clark","textObjs":[{"text":"And you suggest --","start":963.184,"stop":964.064,"duration":0.88}]},{"speakerName":"Potter Stewart","textObjs":[{"text":"Excuse me -- the usual thing to do, isn't it?","start":964.064,"stop":965.775,"duration":1.71}]},{"speakerName":"H. Alva Brumfield","textObjs":[{"text":"That's the usual thing to do.","start":965.775,"stop":966.835,"duration":1.06},{"text":"For example, we can file a suit direct against the insurance company --","start":966.835,"stop":970.808,"duration":3.97}]},{"speakerName":"Potter Stewart","textObjs":[{"text":"(Inaudible)","start":970.808,"stop":971.107,"duration":0.3}]},{"speakerName":"H. Alva Brumfield","textObjs":[{"text":"-- without naming the insured and this Court has upheld in the landmark decisions insofar as we are concerned in Louisiana.","start":971.107,"stop":979.042,"duration":7.94},{"text":"Mr. Chief Justice Warren, the organ of one of those decisions upholding the -- that statute.","start":979.042,"stop":984.74,"duration":5.7}]},{"speakerName":"Arthur J. Goldberg","textObjs":[{"text":"Do you interpret the (Inaudible)","start":984.74,"stop":996.47,"duration":11.73}]},{"speakerName":"H. Alva Brumfield","textObjs":[{"text":"No -- no, I would -- it may have influenced it, Mr. Justice Goldberg, because of course --","start":996.47,"stop":1002.317,"duration":5.85}]},{"speakerName":"Byron R. White","textObjs":[{"text":"(Inaudible)","start":1002.317,"stop":1003.976,"duration":1.66}]},{"speakerName":"H. Alva Brumfield","textObjs":[{"text":"Sir?","start":1003.976,"stop":1004.564,"duration":0.59}]},{"speakerName":"Byron R. White","textObjs":[{"text":"Then it should've been (Inaudible)","start":1004.564,"stop":1005.749,"duration":1.19}]},{"speakerName":"H. Alva Brumfield","textObjs":[{"text":"And -- and it shouldn't -- shouldn't have been.","start":1005.749,"stop":1007.635,"duration":1.89}]},{"speakerName":"Byron R. White","textObjs":[{"text":"(Inaudible)","start":1007.635,"stop":1008.372,"duration":0.74}]},{"speakerName":"H. Alva Brumfield","textObjs":[{"text":"Because we and the -- we and the federal court here and the rules with regard to the sufficiency of the evidence is laid down by this Court in -- in countless decisions that where you have a -- a conflict in evidence and -- and inferences may be drawn by that conflicting evidence by a jury and the jury makes that decision then the decisions of this Court is in fact that that jury verdict stands.","start":1008.372,"stop":1040.265,"duration":31.89},{"text":"And that it is not permissible for the appellate court, the Circuit Court to substitute or make a redertermination or to weigh the evidence in order to -- to make a determination of the facts itself.","start":1040.265,"stop":1056.955,"duration":16.69},{"text":"And often times, in many decisions of this Court, you have upheld the jury verdict even though if you were called upon to make that decision of finding the fact, you wouldn't have -- have made the same finding of fact.","start":1056.955,"stop":1072.962,"duration":16.01},{"text":"And I think that -- that's true in the diversity cases of Mr. -- either Justice Goldberg in one of a case that I found that -- that is as close to this as -- as any case that -- was the Dick case versus New York Life.","start":1072.962,"stop":1091.395,"duration":18.43},{"text":"Mr. Chief Justice Warren was the organ of the Court, a question of -- of whether or not on a -- on a policy it was an accidental death or suicide and a -- the shot of a gun going off and -- and the jury found that it was an accident, not suicide.","start":1091.395,"stop":1109.457,"duration":18.06},{"text":"In -- and the Court of Appeal reversed it and this Court reinstated that jury verdict by -- by stating that there was a sufficiency of evidence to -- to support that finding of the jury.","start":1109.457,"stop":1122.239,"duration":12.78}]},{"speakerName":"Arthur J. Goldberg","textObjs":[{"text":"(Inaudible)","start":1122.239,"stop":1123.076,"duration":0.84}]},{"speakerName":"H. Alva Brumfield","textObjs":[{"text":"Yes.","start":1123.076,"stop":1123.781,"duration":0.7}]},{"speakerName":"Arthur J. Goldberg","textObjs":[{"text":"(Inaudible)","start":1123.781,"stop":1145.468,"duration":21.69}]},{"speakerName":"H. Alva Brumfield","textObjs":[{"text":"Well, that's true.","start":1145.468,"stop":1146.153,"duration":0.68}]},{"speakerName":"Arthur J. Goldberg","textObjs":[{"text":"(Inaudible)","start":1146.153,"stop":1147.132,"duration":0.98}]},{"speakerName":"H. Alva Brumfield","textObjs":[{"text":"It -- that's --","start":1147.132,"stop":1147.899,"duration":0.77}]},{"speakerName":"Arthur J. Goldberg","textObjs":[{"text":"(Inaudible)","start":1147.899,"stop":1152.91,"duration":5.01}]},{"speakerName":"H. Alva Brumfield","textObjs":[{"text":"Yes --","start":1152.91,"stop":1153.188,"duration":0.28}]},{"speakerName":"Arthur J. Goldberg","textObjs":[{"text":"(Inaudible)","start":1153.188,"stop":1154.35,"duration":1.16}]},{"speakerName":"H. Alva Brumfield","textObjs":[{"text":"The federal standard when it should be and I know this many --","start":1154.35,"stop":1156.817,"duration":2.47}]},{"speakerName":"Potter Stewart","textObjs":[{"text":"But -- but you're saying that so far as the right to a trial de novo in a Court of Appeals goes, that's been settled (Inaudible) -- that if -- once you're in the federal courts, you don't get that.","start":1156.817,"stop":1165.814,"duration":9}]},{"speakerName":"H. Alva Brumfield","textObjs":[{"text":"You don't get that --","start":1165.814,"stop":1166.921,"duration":1.11}]},{"speakerName":"Potter Stewart","textObjs":[{"text":"No.","start":1166.921,"stop":1167.131,"duration":0.21}]},{"speakerName":"H. Alva Brumfield","textObjs":[{"text":"-- in the federal court.","start":1167.131,"stop":1168.687,"duration":1.56},{"text":"And -- and the sufficiency of the evidence rule, you'd have to use the federal rule on that because we just don't have one in Louisiana, and that's just what it amounts to.","start":1168.687,"stop":1178.005,"duration":9.32}]},{"speakerName":"Hugo L. Black","textObjs":[{"text":"(Inaudible)","start":1178.005,"stop":1178.721,"duration":0.72}]},{"speakerName":"Potter Stewart","textObjs":[{"text":"I see what you mean.","start":1178.721,"stop":1179.214,"duration":0.49}]},{"speakerName":"Hugo L. Black","textObjs":[{"text":"But I think that there were -- had held that in a case a long time ago that even where facts were determined by the jury in a state court, that case gets moved over here that this Court is bound to respect the verdict of that jury --","start":1179.214,"stop":1196.465,"duration":17.25}]},{"speakerName":"H. Alva Brumfield","textObjs":[{"text":"Yes, sir.","start":1196.465,"stop":1196.614,"duration":0.15}]},{"speakerName":"Hugo L. Black","textObjs":[{"text":"-- when it -- the regular standard.","start":1196.614,"stop":1198.084,"duration":1.47}]},{"speakerName":"Hugo L. Black","textObjs":[{"text":"Yes, sir -- Judge, that's exactly right.","start":1198.084,"stop":1199.98,"duration":1.9}]},{"speakerName":"Hugo L. Black","textObjs":[{"text":"And cannot upset it --","start":1199.98,"stop":1201.642,"duration":1.66}]},{"speakerName":"H. Alva Brumfield","textObjs":[{"text":"We cannot upset it.","start":1201.642,"stop":1203.464,"duration":1.82},{"text":"And -- and that is the -- the position that that we take here and -- and when the -- and when the -- the Fifth Circuit Court of Appeal remanded this case that attached to it a mandate to go out and -- and find some -- some evidence that would support a jury verdict and have a -- some sort of a hearing before the trial judge and then he would decide whether or not that should be at -- a trial by jury.","start":1203.464,"stop":1232.826,"duration":29.36},{"text":"I -- I just -- I was frustrated in -- excuse me.","start":1232.826,"stop":1236.434,"duration":3.61}]},{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"We'll recess now Mr. --","start":1236.434,"stop":1238.591,"duration":2.16}]}]},{"transcriptTitle":"Oral Argument - April 22, 1964 (Part 2)","transcriptLink":"https://apps.oyez.org/player/#/warren11/oral_argument_audio/14557","transcript":[{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"Mr. Brumfield, you may continue your argument.","start":0,"stop":4.605,"duration":4.61}]},{"speakerName":"H. Alva Brumfield","textObjs":[{"text":"May it please the Court.","start":4.605,"stop":7.491,"duration":2.89},{"text":"I would like to reserve my 11 minutes, I believe I have --","start":7.491,"stop":10.574,"duration":3.08}]},{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"You -- you may --","start":10.574,"stop":10.669,"duration":0.1}]},{"speakerName":"H. Alva Brumfield","textObjs":[{"text":"-- enough for rebuttal.","start":10.669,"stop":11.457,"duration":0.79}]},{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"You may Mr. Brumfield.","start":11.457,"stop":12.312,"duration":0.85}]},{"speakerName":"H. Alva Brumfield","textObjs":[{"text":"Thank you -- thank you sir.","start":12.312,"stop":13.169,"duration":0.86}]},{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"Mr. Loeb.","start":13.169,"stop":15.425,"duration":2.26}]},{"speakerName":"Stanley E. Loeb","textObjs":[{"text":"Thank you.","start":15.425,"stop":16.222,"duration":0.8},{"text":"Mr. Chief Justice, members of the Court.","start":16.222,"stop":23.952,"duration":7.73},{"text":"Mr. Brumfield has stated the facts of the case and I would like to pick up in the discussion of the Dick versus New York Life Insurance Company decision, which as Mr. Justice Goldberg pointed out, has left open the question of whether the sufficiency of evidence is -- could be measured by state law or by federal law.","start":23.952,"stop":54.219,"duration":30.27},{"text":"That might be an open question but in the same decision, there is found the falsity of statement that under the area rule, presumptions and burden of proof in the diversity case are substantive in the matters of state law.","start":54.219,"stop":74.476,"duration":20.26},{"text":"And the law of Louisiana, the substantive law of Louisiana presumes that a motorist or everybody else obeys the law.","start":74.476,"stop":88.318,"duration":13.84},{"text":"There is no presumption of negligence, presumption as it -- just to the contrary.","start":88.318,"stop":94.705,"duration":6.39},{"text":"And the decisions of our Supreme Court are clear that in a case of this kind predicated on Article 2315 of our Civil Code which is cited on the first page of respondent's brief in a footnote puts upon the plaintiff the burden of proof of all the elements necessary to establish liability.","start":94.705,"stop":124.23,"duration":29.53},{"text":"In a case like this where there was no witness to the accident, the first element of proof is that this -- the defendant was a party to the accident.","start":124.23,"stop":135.735,"duration":11.51},{"text":"And the second element, which had -- the defendant was negligent.","start":135.735,"stop":141.039,"duration":5.3},{"text":"Now, this case, after the jury found for the plaintiff was appealed to the Court of Appeals for the Fifth Circuit and Chief Judge -- then Chief Judge Hutcheson wrote the opinion for the Court.","start":141.039,"stop":160.963,"duration":19.92},{"text":"And he carefully avoided reference to any State decision in arriving at the conclusion that the evidence was not sufficient to support the verdict, number one.","start":160.963,"stop":173.738,"duration":12.78},{"text":"And second, that the record was literally thought with reversible error.","start":173.738,"stop":182.236,"duration":8.5},{"text":"Apparently, the reversible error question is not before Your Honors.","start":182.236,"stop":186.254,"duration":4.02},{"text":"It was not raised in petitioner's brief and I comment it in respondent's brief, that such was the case on page 14.","start":186.254,"stop":201.755,"duration":15.5},{"text":"I -- the comment is made that petitioner has not discussed in her brief the holding of the Court of Appeals on the first appeal that there was reversible error.","start":201.755,"stop":212.657,"duration":10.9},{"text":"But --","start":212.657,"stop":214.398,"duration":1.74}]},{"speakerName":"Hugo L. Black","textObjs":[{"text":"But that would be before us anyhow, would it not?","start":214.398,"stop":216.825,"duration":2.43}]},{"speakerName":"Stanley E. Loeb","textObjs":[{"text":"I believe so.","start":216.825,"stop":218.248,"duration":1.42},{"text":"I believe it's before you.","start":218.248,"stop":219.456,"duration":1.21},{"text":"Perhaps I used the wrong word Mr. Justice Black.","start":219.456,"stop":221.829,"duration":2.37},{"text":"It's before you, the whole case is before you but I meant that the issue hasn't been raised in petitioner's -- either petition or in their brief in this particular case.","start":221.829,"stop":236.174,"duration":14.35},{"text":"The problem now seems to be directed toward the mandate of the Court of Appeals in the first appeal.","start":236.174,"stop":245.102,"duration":8.93},{"text":"And it is as Mr. Brumfield has pointed out a most unusual mandate.","start":245.102,"stop":250.518,"duration":5.42},{"text":"And it seems to me that this Court's attention was attracted by the mandate in its respect to the Seventh Amendment.","start":250.518,"stop":260.245,"duration":9.73},{"text":"With the permission of the Court, I will read the mandate.\"","start":260.245,"stop":265.284,"duration":5.04},{"text":"Because however, evidence as distinguished from rumor and speculation as to the why and how of the death of plaintiff-decedent and as to the responsibility of the defendant for it, may have been or maybe discovered.","start":265.284,"stop":282.798,"duration":17.51},{"text":"We order the judgment reversed and the cause remanded with directions to enter a judgment for defendant.","start":282.798,"stop":289.646,"duration":6.85},{"text":"Unless plaintiff, within a time and under considerations to be fixed by the district judge, makes a satisfactory showing that on another trial, evidence of sufficient probative force to justify submission of the case to the jury will be open.","start":289.646,"stop":306.711,"duration":17.06},{"text":"In which case, the judgment shall be for a new trial.\"","start":306.711,"stop":311.552,"duration":4.84},{"text":"So what the Court of Appeals did was to remand the case to the District Court to allow the plaintiff to make out to the satisfaction of the district judge, with Judge Wright, that on another trial she could produce evidence of sufficient probative force -- force to take the case to the jury.","start":311.552,"stop":336.397,"duration":24.84},{"text":"Now, what happened was, plaintiff timely filed an appropriate motion for a new trial and in support of that motion and on the order of the District Court, some nine or 10 depositions were taken including the depositions of some of the witnesses who had testified on the trial.","start":336.397,"stop":359.549,"duration":23.15},{"text":"In addition to that, there was an ex parte report from an accident technician or purported accident technician which was all submitted to Judge Wright.","start":359.549,"stop":370.226,"duration":10.68},{"text":"Judge Wright considered the motion and the evidence submitted in support of the motion in light of the mandate and ruled that there was nothing in the evidence submitted in support of the mandate to -- to support the conclusion that on another trial there would be probative evidence that could go to the jury.","start":370.226,"stop":397.546,"duration":27.32},{"text":"Therefore, he refused the new trial.","start":397.546,"stop":400.451,"duration":2.91},{"text":"Plaintiff asked for a rehearing and the rehearing was granted.","start":400.451,"stop":404.795,"duration":4.34},{"text":"The argument was heard.","start":404.795,"stop":406.918,"duration":2.12},{"text":"And if the Court please, that was when I came into the case.","start":406.918,"stop":411.059,"duration":4.14},{"text":"My predecessor, who is Mr. Robert G. Hughes, was elected to the bench after the case was tried and after the case was argued and after the Fifth Circuit had ruled on it.","start":411.059,"stop":422.901,"duration":11.84},{"text":"And I came into the case when he was elevated to the state bench and picked it up at the second -- at the first rehearing, the second argument on the motion for a new trial before Judge Wright.","start":422.901,"stop":437.496,"duration":14.59},{"text":"Judge Wright again considered and refused a new trial.","start":437.496,"stop":442.512,"duration":5.02},{"text":"Thereupon, plaintiff appealed again to the Court of Appeals seeking review and getting review of Judge Wright's rulings.","start":442.512,"stop":452.591,"duration":10.08},{"text":"That case was argued to a panel of the Court and a few weeks thereafter, counsel were notified that the panel would submit it to the whole court en banc and additional briefs could be submitted, that was done and the whole Court considered the matter and rendered the opinion in the second appeal affirming Judge Wright's refusal of a new trial by a divided court, five-to-four with Chief Judge Reeves filing a dissent.","start":452.591,"stop":484.362,"duration":31.77},{"text":"In his dissent, it's leveled with the Seventh Amendment and that raises in my mind the notion that that is the crux of this case whether the mandate, the original mandate, has done violence to the Seventh Amendment, because I know this Court is busy and has not concerned itself with the particular facts of a particular diversity suit.","start":484.362,"stop":509.45,"duration":25.09},{"text":"But the -- the Seventh Amendment feature of the case is the important one as I see it.","start":509.45,"stop":517.769,"duration":8.32},{"text":"Now, in the Slocum case, this Court speaking through Mr. Justice Van Devanter said in 19 -- I think 1930 that, \"Everything of a phiso -- philosophical nature concerning the Seventh Amendment which could be said at that time had been said.","start":517.769,"stop":539.154,"duration":21.38},{"text":"And there was little to be added to it.","start":539.154,"stop":542.181,"duration":3.03},{"text":"That the Seventh Amendment restricted the scope of appellate review to the -- that is in -- in federal court, to the common law as it existed in 1791, which interpreted means that where the suf -- insufficiency of the evidence is grounds for a reversal.","start":542.181,"stop":570.676,"duration":28.5},{"text":"The Court could grant a new trial and nothing more.\"","start":570.676,"stop":575.236,"duration":4.56},{"text":"That was the rule of common law in effect in 1791.","start":575.236,"stop":581.654,"duration":6.42},{"text":"Now, it is quite apparent that the mandate which I just read does not order a new trial, nor does it deprive the plaintiff of their rights guaranteed by the Seventh Amendment because in the case of Gasoline -- and it's cited in my brief, Products Company versus Champlin which is 380 -- 283 U.S. 494.","start":581.654,"stop":620.001,"duration":38.35},{"text":"This Court held that the Seventh Amendment guarantee did not restrict the appellate courts to the procedure of the common law of 1791.","start":620.001,"stop":632.181,"duration":12.18},{"text":"And the opinion says, \"We're not concerned with form, we're concerned with the substance of the Amendment.\"","start":632.181,"stop":639.523,"duration":7.34},{"text":"And the modern practice even then, was not to be circumscribed because of just blind adherence to the old forms.","start":639.523,"stop":654.216,"duration":14.69},{"text":"Now, in 1960, when this case was remanded, it was remanded with -- and thought in mind that the Federal Rules of Civil Procedure provided the mechanics, the tools whereby the District Court could ascertain in advance of another trial whether the judge would be constrained to direct the verdict at the close of the plaintiff's testimony.","start":654.216,"stop":682.17,"duration":27.95},{"text":"And that's exactly what happened.","start":682.17,"stop":684.077,"duration":1.91},{"text":"The plaintiff had unrestricted opportunity and did produce all of the witnesses he could possibly find.","start":684.077,"stop":692.996,"duration":8.92},{"text":"Those witnesses, as counsel told you in his argument, testified -- well Officer Prudom (ph) said it.","start":692.996,"stop":700.389,"duration":7.39},{"text":"And Officer Prudom (ph) testified that Officer Gidrey (ph) said it and it was a hodge-podge of conflicting rumor, speculation and guess work.","start":700.389,"stop":712.544,"duration":12.15},{"text":"The whole record is here, the original depositions of those witnesses are in the record.","start":712.544,"stop":719.636,"duration":7.09},{"text":"And on the second appeal, the -- which even the dissenting opinion of Judge Reeves pointed out that it was just a conglomerate mass of hearsay which would be inadmissible.","start":719.636,"stop":734.982,"duration":15.35},{"text":"However, Judge Reeves thought that there was one piece of evidence there that was sufficient to take the case to the jury.","start":734.982,"stop":743.35,"duration":8.37},{"text":"And that was apparently the reason for his dissent.","start":743.35,"stop":747.001,"duration":3.65},{"text":"But --","start":747.001,"stop":747.796,"duration":0.8}]},{"speakerName":"Potter Stewart","textObjs":[{"text":"What do -- what -- what piece of evidence was there?","start":747.796,"stop":749.519,"duration":1.72}]},{"speakerName":"Stanley E. Loeb","textObjs":[{"text":"It was a two -- a statement by one of the policemen concerning what he saw at the scene and what he said he saw at the scene of the accident.","start":749.519,"stop":759.882,"duration":10.36}]},{"speakerName":"Potter Stewart","textObjs":[{"text":"What he himself had seen.","start":759.882,"stop":761.34,"duration":1.46}]},{"speakerName":"Stanley E. Loeb","textObjs":[{"text":"He himself, concerning some track -- track marks.","start":761.34,"stop":765.583,"duration":4.24},{"text":"But of course he had no way of knowing what vehicle made the track marks.","start":765.583,"stop":769.109,"duration":3.53}]},{"speakerName":"Potter Stewart","textObjs":[{"text":"Alright.","start":769.109,"stop":770.796,"duration":1.69}]},{"speakerName":"Stanley E. Loeb","textObjs":[{"text":"But except for that one piece of evidence which this -- the patrolman said he saw.","start":770.796,"stop":777.229,"duration":6.43},{"text":"The rest of it is merely speculation.","start":777.229,"stop":780.892,"duration":3.66}]},{"speakerName":"Arthur J. Goldberg","textObjs":[{"text":"Assuming Mr. Loeb --","start":780.892,"stop":781.922,"duration":1.03}]},{"speakerName":"Stanley E. Loeb","textObjs":[{"text":"Yes, sir.","start":781.922,"stop":783.424,"duration":1.5}]},{"speakerName":"Arthur J. Goldberg","textObjs":[{"text":"-- we were (Inaudible)","start":783.424,"stop":794.919,"duration":11.5}]},{"speakerName":"Stanley E. Loeb","textObjs":[{"text":"There is no question about that.","start":794.919,"stop":796.786,"duration":1.87}]},{"speakerName":"Arthur J. Goldberg","textObjs":[{"text":"(Inaudible)","start":796.786,"stop":803.292,"duration":6.51}]},{"speakerName":"Stanley E. Loeb","textObjs":[{"text":"Well sir, that had been an open question since the Dick decision and I believe that I'm not going to evade your question, Mr. Justice, but I believe whatever standard that might be applied in this case, be it state or federal, and reading of the record and of the opinion of the Court of Appeals in the first opinion, will immediately show that a remand was necessary.","start":803.292,"stop":833.247,"duration":29.95},{"text":"There was no evidence at all to support the verdict.","start":833.247,"stop":837.739,"duration":4.49},{"text":"And beyond that, there were many instances of reversible error.","start":837.739,"stop":843.102,"duration":5.36}]},{"speakerName":"Byron R. White","textObjs":[{"text":"Well you don't say then the wrong --- you don't question but what the Court of Appeals used the right standard in reviewing the case.","start":843.102,"stop":851.066,"duration":7.96}]},{"speakerName":"Stanley E. Loeb","textObjs":[{"text":"Oh, they did.","start":851.066,"stop":851.665,"duration":0.6},{"text":"They did sir.","start":851.665,"stop":852.429,"duration":0.76},{"text":"They used the right standard.","start":852.429,"stop":853.706,"duration":1.28},{"text":"And whatever standard they might have used, it would have been the same.","start":853.706,"stop":858.666,"duration":4.96},{"text":"I doubt that the federal standard --","start":858.666,"stop":862.081,"duration":3.41}]},{"speakerName":"Byron R. White","textObjs":[{"text":"Well, there is no (Voice Overlap) --","start":862.081,"stop":862.561,"duration":0.48}]},{"speakerName":"Stanley E. Loeb","textObjs":[{"text":"-- if there'd be one.","start":862.561,"stop":864.111,"duration":1.55}]},{"speakerName":"Byron R. White","textObjs":[{"text":"Well, there is no Louisiana standard to the --","start":864.111,"stop":865.934,"duration":1.82}]},{"speakerName":"Stanley E. Loeb","textObjs":[{"text":"I think there is and I would differ with the counsel there.","start":865.934,"stop":868.916,"duration":2.98},{"text":"There is because whereas all appellate courts have the power, the constitutional power in our state constitution to review findings of fact by the trial -- by -- by the finders of fact, judge or jury.","start":868.916,"stop":886.136,"duration":17.22},{"text":"There still is a standard of sufficiency of the evidence to support a finding of fact, be it a verdict or finding of fact by a judge.","start":886.136,"stop":898.053,"duration":11.92},{"text":"And it's a very real standard.","start":898.053,"stop":900.611,"duration":2.56}]},{"speakerName":"Arthur J. Goldberg","textObjs":[{"text":"(Inaudible)","start":900.611,"stop":902.345,"duration":1.73}]},{"speakerName":"Stanley E. Loeb","textObjs":[{"text":"No difference.","start":902.345,"stop":902.914,"duration":0.57}]},{"speakerName":"Arthur J. Goldberg","textObjs":[{"text":"(Inaudible)","start":902.914,"stop":904.33,"duration":1.42}]},{"speakerName":"Stanley E. Loeb","textObjs":[{"text":"No different from the standard in any other state because counsel properly told you that our state law of torts is the general -- it has no gimmicks in it.","start":904.33,"stop":915.951,"duration":11.62}]},{"speakerName":"Arthur J. Goldberg","textObjs":[{"text":"And no different from the federal standard in reviewing it.","start":915.951,"stop":918.809,"duration":2.86}]},{"speakerName":"Stanley E. Loeb","textObjs":[{"text":"If Your Honor please, I don't know what the federal standard of review is.","start":918.809,"stop":923.285,"duration":4.48},{"text":"I don't know whether there is a separate standard.","start":923.285,"stop":928.545,"duration":5.26},{"text":"In the Dick case, Mr. Chief Justice left the question open and --","start":928.545,"stop":935.935,"duration":7.39}]},{"speakerName":"Byron R. White","textObjs":[{"text":"Well for example, does the Louisiana have that thing called (Inaudible)?","start":935.935,"stop":944.453,"duration":8.52}]},{"speakerName":"Stanley E. Loeb","textObjs":[{"text":"No.","start":944.453,"stop":946.288,"duration":1.84},{"text":"I would say no.","start":946.288,"stop":947.093,"duration":0.8}]},{"speakerName":"Byron R. White","textObjs":[{"text":"That's placed insufficient evidence --","start":947.093,"stop":949.727,"duration":2.63}]},{"speakerName":"Stanley E. Loeb","textObjs":[{"text":"Sufficient evidence.","start":949.727,"stop":951.176,"duration":1.45},{"text":"Evidence of such property force as would cause man of intelligence do differ.","start":951.176,"stop":960.897,"duration":9.72},{"text":"That seems to be the standard in Louisiana and if there be a federal standard, Mr. Justice White I suggest that that would apparently be it.","start":960.897,"stop":970.035,"duration":9.14}]},{"speakerName":"Potter Stewart","textObjs":[{"text":"Mr. Loeb --","start":970.035,"stop":970.946,"duration":0.91}]},{"speakerName":"Stanley E. Loeb","textObjs":[{"text":"Yes sir.","start":970.946,"stop":971.334,"duration":0.39}]},{"speakerName":"Potter Stewart","textObjs":[{"text":"Is -- doesn't it remain true in Louisiana and as I understand it uniquely in Louisiana that an appellate court, even if it might find that the evidence were sufficient to support a particular finding of fact could -- would still have the power to say, nonetheless, we think that the preponderance of the evidence shows the facts to be just the opposite and we therefore are so find.","start":971.334,"stop":993.279,"duration":21.95}]},{"speakerName":"Stanley E. Loeb","textObjs":[{"text":"That is correct.","start":993.279,"stop":994.397,"duration":1.12}]},{"speakerName":"Potter Stewart","textObjs":[{"text":"So to that extent, you don't -- you're not limited by efficiency of the evidence standard as are the federal courts and are -- as are the courts of all the other states to the best of my knowledge, isn't that correct?","start":994.397,"stop":1006.552,"duration":12.15}]},{"speakerName":"Stanley E. Loeb","textObjs":[{"text":"I -- I'm afraid that that is stated in such a way Mr. Justice that it --","start":1006.552,"stop":1010.986,"duration":4.43}]},{"speakerName":"Potter Stewart","textObjs":[{"text":"I didn't mean to be unfair.","start":1010.986,"stop":1012.016,"duration":1.03},{"text":"I'm really --","start":1012.016,"stop":1012.397,"duration":0.38}]},{"speakerName":"Stanley E. Loeb","textObjs":[{"text":"It's difficult to answer.","start":1012.397,"stop":1014.383,"duration":1.99}]},{"speakerName":"Potter Stewart","textObjs":[{"text":"You -- you --","start":1014.383,"stop":1014.618,"duration":0.24}]},{"speakerName":"Stanley E. Loeb","textObjs":[{"text":"The --","start":1014.618,"stop":1015.227,"duration":0.61}]},{"speakerName":"Potter Stewart","textObjs":[{"text":"-- rephrased my question anyway.","start":1015.227,"stop":1017.875,"duration":2.65}]},{"speakerName":"Stanley E. Loeb","textObjs":[{"text":"Well, as the -- the appellate courts do have the power to find facts different from the -- that -- those facts found by the trier of fact.","start":1017.875,"stop":1028.333,"duration":10.46}]},{"speakerName":"Potter Stewart","textObjs":[{"text":"And -- and may I interrupt to ask --","start":1028.333,"stop":1030.06,"duration":1.73}]},{"speakerName":"Stanley E. Loeb","textObjs":[{"text":"(Voice Overlap)","start":1030.06,"stop":1030.262,"duration":0.2}]},{"speakerName":"Potter Stewart","textObjs":[{"text":"-- do they have that power even if it's assumed that there might be sufficient evidence to support the triers of findings.","start":1030.262,"stop":1039.959,"duration":9.7}]},{"speakerName":"Stanley E. Loeb","textObjs":[{"text":"I didn't get that.","start":1039.959,"stop":1041.425,"duration":1.47},{"text":"That they have the power regardless, they have the power.","start":1041.425,"stop":1044.858,"duration":3.43}]},{"speakerName":"Potter Stewart","textObjs":[{"text":"Yes.","start":1044.858,"stop":1046.281,"duration":1.42}]},{"speakerName":"Stanley E. Loeb","textObjs":[{"text":"But, there is the uniform rule established by the jurisprudent that the power will never be exercised except in case of palpable error.","start":1046.281,"stop":1059.859,"duration":13.58},{"text":"Now, if there's no error shown by the record, the -- the appellate courts under the jurisprudence and the recent jurisprudence of Louisiana Supreme Court.","start":1059.859,"stop":1070.089,"duration":10.23},{"text":"The -- under that rule, which is firmly established, the appellate courts shall not interfere with the finding of fact unless there is apparent error on the part of the trier of fact.","start":1070.089,"stop":1086.689,"duration":16.6},{"text":"So you do have a rule, a very real rule, which is adhered to.","start":1086.689,"stop":1093.685,"duration":7},{"text":"Now, of course, in Louisiana we have four Circuit Courts of Appeal, the intermediary courts and one Supreme Court.","start":1093.685,"stop":1100.914,"duration":7.23},{"text":"Now, I don't mean to tell you that every case where one of the Circuit Courts of Appeals might undertake to reverse a jury or -- or a judge -- trial judge.","start":1100.914,"stop":1110.605,"duration":9.69},{"text":"That in every case there is palpable error that the Court thinks so because they are -- they are bound, they did -- the Courts of Appeal are bound by the decisions of our Supreme Court on the Circuit.","start":1110.605,"stop":1123.206,"duration":12.6},{"text":"So we do have a rule and I doubt as I say it again, except for the scintilla rule which I don't know whether that constitutes a federal rule or not.","start":1123.206,"stop":1134.687,"duration":11.48}]},{"speakerName":"Potter Stewart","textObjs":[{"text":"Well, I suppose it would --","start":1134.687,"stop":1135.141,"duration":0.45}]},{"speakerName":"Stanley E. Loeb","textObjs":[{"text":"It might and it would -- excuse me sir.","start":1135.141,"stop":1136.079,"duration":0.94}]},{"speakerName":"Potter Stewart","textObjs":[{"text":"Excuse me sir.","start":1136.079,"stop":1137.27,"duration":1.19}]},{"speakerName":"Stanley E. Loeb","textObjs":[{"text":"It might at a Workmen's Compensation situation.","start":1137.27,"stop":1139.871,"duration":2.6}]},{"speakerName":"Potter Stewart","textObjs":[{"text":"I was -- because that's a -- you rephrase the question I was going to ask you.","start":1139.871,"stop":1143.243,"duration":3.37},{"text":"I suppose if -- if the federal rule were to be found in the Federal Employers' Liability Act cases, for instance and that is -- it might differ somewhat at least from the -- the rule as to the sufficiency of the evidence standards and -- and in the (Voice Overlap) --","start":1143.243,"stop":1159.055,"duration":15.81}]},{"speakerName":"Stanley E. Loeb","textObjs":[{"text":"It certainly would.","start":1159.055,"stop":1159.341,"duration":0.29}]},{"speakerName":"Potter Stewart","textObjs":[{"text":"-- in the United States.","start":1159.341,"stop":1160.478,"duration":1.14}]},{"speakerName":"Stanley E. Loeb","textObjs":[{"text":"It certainly would.","start":1160.478,"stop":1161.119,"duration":0.64},{"text":"And if -- of course we were trying in the state court a Jones Act suit.","start":1161.119,"stop":1165.376,"duration":4.26}]},{"speakerName":"Potter Stewart","textObjs":[{"text":"Yes.","start":1165.376,"stop":1165.966,"duration":0.59}]},{"speakerName":"Stanley E. Loeb","textObjs":[{"text":"An FELA case.","start":1165.966,"stop":1166.906,"duration":0.94}]},{"speakerName":"Potter Stewart","textObjs":[{"text":"Yes.","start":1166.906,"stop":1168.159,"duration":1.25}]},{"speakerName":"Stanley E. Loeb","textObjs":[{"text":"The scintilla rule would apply.","start":1168.159,"stop":1170.849,"duration":2.69},{"text":"The --","start":1170.849,"stop":1170.873,"duration":0.02}]},{"speakerName":"Potter Stewart","textObjs":[{"text":"I know, that's ever been --","start":1170.873,"stop":1172.155,"duration":1.28}]},{"speakerName":"Stanley E. Loeb","textObjs":[{"text":"I don't --","start":1172.155,"stop":1172.289,"duration":0.13}]},{"speakerName":"Potter Stewart","textObjs":[{"text":"-- verbalized that way.","start":1172.289,"stop":1173.218,"duration":0.93}]},{"speakerName":"Stanley E. Loeb","textObjs":[{"text":"I don't know.","start":1173.218,"stop":1173.864,"duration":0.65}]},{"speakerName":"Potter Stewart","textObjs":[{"text":"I agree with you that --","start":1173.864,"stop":1174.592,"duration":0.73}]},{"speakerName":"Stanley E. Loeb","textObjs":[{"text":"But certainly the --","start":1174.592,"stop":1175.432,"duration":0.84}]},{"speakerName":"Potter Stewart","textObjs":[{"text":"(Voice Overlap)","start":1175.432,"stop":1176.46,"duration":1.03}]},{"speakerName":"Stanley E. Loeb","textObjs":[{"text":"The burden -- the extent of proof necessary would not be as great and that -- incidentally, that is apparent in this record and in the briefs and the cases cited by the petitioner, their mostly FELA cases.","start":1176.46,"stop":1190.882,"duration":14.42},{"text":"But even this Court in an FELA case and the Moore case, Moore versus the Chesapeake and Ohio Railroad, reviewed the effect -- Justice -- Fifth Circuit did here and found there was no evidence to support the -- the verdict of the jury.","start":1190.882,"stop":1210.49,"duration":19.61}]},{"speakerName":"Arthur J. Goldberg","textObjs":[{"text":"(Inaudible)","start":1210.49,"stop":1225.645,"duration":15.15}]},{"speakerName":"Stanley E. Loeb","textObjs":[{"text":"Yes sir.","start":1225.645,"stop":1226.027,"duration":0.38}]},{"speakerName":"Arthur J. Goldberg","textObjs":[{"text":"(Inaudible)","start":1226.027,"stop":1226.907,"duration":0.88}]},{"speakerName":"Stanley E. Loeb","textObjs":[{"text":"Yes sir.","start":1226.907,"stop":1227.936,"duration":1.03}]},{"speakerName":"Arthur J. Goldberg","textObjs":[{"text":"(Inaudible)","start":1227.936,"stop":1244.045,"duration":16.11}]},{"speakerName":"Stanley E. Loeb","textObjs":[{"text":"Not only of a -- they exposed to, they are bound to by -- by our civil code and by the decisions of the Supreme Court.","start":1244.045,"stop":1251.623,"duration":7.58}]},{"speakerName":"Arthur J. Goldberg","textObjs":[{"text":"(Inaudible)","start":1251.623,"stop":1267.289,"duration":15.67}]},{"speakerName":"Stanley E. Loeb","textObjs":[{"text":"I would -- oh yes.","start":1267.289,"stop":1268.138,"duration":0.85},{"text":"Except -- except for that instance which was very important because the correction didn't occur until long after.","start":1268.138,"stop":1273.538,"duration":5.4}]},{"speakerName":"Arthur J. Goldberg","textObjs":[{"text":"(Inaudible)","start":1273.538,"stop":1280.243,"duration":6.7}]},{"speakerName":"Stanley E. Loeb","textObjs":[{"text":"Correct, Judge Wright correctly stated the law of Louisiana on -- on negligence.","start":1280.243,"stop":1284.755,"duration":4.51}]},{"speakerName":"Arthur J. Goldberg","textObjs":[{"text":"Your argument therefore (Inaudible)","start":1284.755,"stop":1287.369,"duration":2.61}]},{"speakerName":"Stanley E. Loeb","textObjs":[{"text":"Please --","start":1287.369,"stop":1287.844,"duration":0.48}]},{"speakerName":"Arthur J. Goldberg","textObjs":[{"text":"(Inaudible)","start":1287.844,"stop":1311.322,"duration":23.48}]},{"speakerName":"Stanley E. Loeb","textObjs":[{"text":"Yes sir.","start":1311.322,"stop":1313.445,"duration":2.12},{"text":"And then it takes us to the mandate whether the mandate --","start":1313.445,"stop":1317.104,"duration":3.66}]},{"speakerName":"Arthur J. Goldberg","textObjs":[{"text":"(Inaudible)","start":1317.104,"stop":1318.578,"duration":1.47}]},{"speakerName":"Stanley E. Loeb","textObjs":[{"text":"Where -- where there was a proper disposition of a case.","start":1318.578,"stop":1321.037,"duration":2.46}]},{"speakerName":"Arthur J. Goldberg","textObjs":[{"text":"(Inaudible)","start":1321.037,"stop":1328.813,"duration":7.78}]},{"speakerName":"Stanley E. Loeb","textObjs":[{"text":"No sir.","start":1328.813,"stop":1329.439,"duration":0.63}]},{"speakerName":"Arthur J. Goldberg","textObjs":[{"text":"(Inaudible)","start":1329.439,"stop":1339.444,"duration":10}]},{"speakerName":"Stanley E. Loeb","textObjs":[{"text":"That's correct.","start":1339.444,"stop":1340.805,"duration":1.36},{"text":"That is correct and since Mr. Justice Goldberg has stated my point, I will thank Your Honors for your attention.","start":1340.805,"stop":1349.879,"duration":9.07}]},{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"Thank you.","start":1349.879,"stop":1351.878,"duration":2},{"text":"Mr. Brumfield.","start":1351.878,"stop":1353.33,"duration":1.45}]},{"speakerName":"H. Alva Brumfield","textObjs":[{"text":"Mr. Chief Justice, as was pointed out by Mr. Justice Goldberg the -- the real issue in this case is whether there was substantial evidence from which the jury could reasonably conclude that the defendant killed Byrd (ph) Mercer.","start":1353.33,"stop":1376.252,"duration":22.92},{"text":"Now, in -- in viewing the entire record, it is our position that there is that evidence in this record regardless of -- of the depositions and other steps that were taken like the report from the accident analyst and the deposition of witnesses that didn't appear at the trial.","start":1376.252,"stop":1399.648,"duration":23.4},{"text":"Irregardless of that, the evidence as educed on the trial with the merits of this case before the jury was sufficient to -- to make a jury question to be submitted to the jury.","start":1399.648,"stop":1412.905,"duration":13.26},{"text":"There was a conflict in the evidence.","start":1412.905,"stop":1416.154,"duration":3.25},{"text":"There were denials by the defendant.","start":1416.154,"stop":1420.473,"duration":4.32},{"text":"There were -- there was testimony to the fact that he was not telling the truth.","start":1420.473,"stop":1427.691,"duration":7.22},{"text":"There were circumstances, there were physical evidence, there were photographs, there was a timing, there were all of these -- the evidence from which a jury could draw inferences and wherever you have that situation as I appreciate the countless decisions handed out by this Court that where you have a conflict of evidence and you -- you have it at that stage where the jury can draw inferences and arrive at a decision and reach a decision as to the fact then that should be submitted to the jury and as a jury question.","start":1427.691,"stop":1467.881,"duration":40.19}]},{"speakerName":"Byron R. White","textObjs":[{"text":"Well, what would the --And then on --","start":1467.881,"stop":1469.229,"duration":1.35}]},{"speakerName":"Byron R. White","textObjs":[{"text":"There may be evidence here that -- that the defendant ran over somebody and that even that he ran over this person who was killed, what's the evidence -- what's the evidence, any evidence that meant that he was negligent in so do -- that he was negligent in so doing it.","start":1469.229,"stop":1485.926,"duration":16.7}]},{"speakerName":"H. Alva Brumfield","textObjs":[{"text":"Well -- well with -- with the man walking down the road, on the shoulder of the road, we had a right to be --","start":1485.926,"stop":1492.215,"duration":6.29}]},{"speakerName":"Byron R. White","textObjs":[{"text":"Well, how do you know he was there?","start":1492.215,"stop":1494.083,"duration":1.87}]},{"speakerName":"H. Alva Brumfield","textObjs":[{"text":"Sir?","start":1494.083,"stop":1494.615,"duration":0.53}]},{"speakerName":"Byron R. White","textObjs":[{"text":"How do you know he was there?","start":1494.615,"stop":1496.184,"duration":1.57}]},{"speakerName":"H. Alva Brumfield","textObjs":[{"text":"Because his body was found there and he was last seen alive at the wharf, he's going his way home.","start":1496.184,"stop":1503.597,"duration":7.41},{"text":"He was going to walk home and not ride.","start":1503.597,"stop":1505.642,"duration":2.05}]},{"speakerName":"Byron R. White","textObjs":[{"text":"But the finding in there doesn't mean he was hit there and that he was walking there.","start":1505.642,"stop":1509.218,"duration":3.58}]},{"speakerName":"H. Alva Brumfield","textObjs":[{"text":"But with the -- with the evidence as shown by the photographs of the tire marks, his position as he was lying there on the shoulder of the road, the -- the blue coloring on the car that struck him --","start":1509.218,"stop":1523.964,"duration":14.75}]},{"speakerName":"Byron R. White","textObjs":[{"text":"Oh yes, but that's just evidence that he was -- that he was struck but what about the negligence of the driver of the truck?","start":1523.964,"stop":1529.236,"duration":5.27}]},{"speakerName":"H. Alva Brumfield","textObjs":[{"text":"Now -- now, the negligence --","start":1529.236,"stop":1530.367,"duration":1.13}]},{"speakerName":"Byron R. White","textObjs":[{"text":"Well, the evidence that -- you have this a -- is that his wheels were off -- were over on the shoulder?","start":1530.367,"stop":1535.008,"duration":4.64}]},{"speakerName":"H. Alva Brumfield","textObjs":[{"text":"Over on the shoulder of the road and you have the deceased there.","start":1535.008,"stop":1538.163,"duration":3.15},{"text":"That it -- that if you prove that, say that you had a witness that was out there in that swamp and saw Theriot drove -- drive off onto the shoulder of the road as Mercer was walking along on the shoulder of that road, that would be direct proof of negligence under the law of Louisiana.","start":1538.163,"stop":1557.823,"duration":19.66},{"text":"Because he wasn't keeping a proper lookout and because he had the last clear chance if nothing else, even if -- if the deceased was negligent himself in walking along on that dark road.","start":1557.823,"stop":1570.173,"duration":12.35},{"text":"The duties is up on the driver of the vehicle in Louisiana to keep his car on a proper control to see what he should've seen, to see all -- to be able to stop his car within the range division of his lights and by not doing that then that would be a preponderance of the evidence showing negligence, which negligence was approximate cause of his death.","start":1570.173,"stop":1592.697,"duration":22.52}]},{"speakerName":"Byron R. White","textObjs":[{"text":"You think in Louisiana, you can show somebody run over somebody else on a -- on a deserted road that -- that evidence of negligence.","start":1592.697,"stop":1599.967,"duration":7.27}]},{"speakerName":"H. Alva Brumfield","textObjs":[{"text":"If he ran off of the -- off of his lane of traffic, of the -- the asphalt portion of the highway and ran into a pedestrian on the shoulder of the highway as his back was to the driver of the automobile that would be absolute passive evidence of negligence without any question.","start":1599.967,"stop":1618.754,"duration":18.79}]},{"speakerName":"Hugo L. Black","textObjs":[{"text":"Suppose he was being tried criminally for that offense?","start":1618.754,"stop":1622.135,"duration":3.38}]},{"speakerName":"H. Alva Brumfield","textObjs":[{"text":"For negligent -- homicide?","start":1622.135,"stop":1623.344,"duration":1.21}]},{"speakerName":"Hugo L. Black","textObjs":[{"text":"In view that he him right at that place.","start":1623.344,"stop":1626.833,"duration":3.49},{"text":"And he claims -- he claims that the he didn't -- he was very careful, could they draw any inference in the fact that he fled after he could --","start":1626.833,"stop":1637.808,"duration":10.97}]},{"speakerName":"H. Alva Brumfield","textObjs":[{"text":"Yes sir.","start":1637.808,"stop":1638.401,"duration":0.59},{"text":"The -- the inference of the fact that he hit and run is a -- is a -- is an inference that can be drawn.","start":1638.401,"stop":1644.982,"duration":6.58},{"text":"And -- and of course in a civil case as Your Honor knows, he -- you don't have to prove it beyond a -- a reasonable doubt as it if -- it was a criminal case.","start":1644.982,"stop":1652.93,"duration":7.95},{"text":"But here, you -- you're not bound with that just by preponderance of the evidence and --","start":1652.93,"stop":1659.067,"duration":6.14}]},{"speakerName":"William J. Brennan, Jr.","textObjs":[{"text":"How about the evidence to be (Inaudible)?","start":1659.067,"stop":1663.763,"duration":4.7}]},{"speakerName":"H. Alva Brumfield","textObjs":[{"text":"I -- I didn't hear you.","start":1663.763,"stop":1664.175,"duration":0.41}]},{"speakerName":"William J. Brennan, Jr.","textObjs":[{"text":"What -- there's some evidence that this defendant had been drinking, did you tell --","start":1664.175,"stop":1667.331,"duration":3.16}]},{"speakerName":"H. Alva Brumfield","textObjs":[{"text":"Oh, there was uncontradicted evidence, he -- the defendant admitted himself that he had been drinking all afternoon.","start":1667.331,"stop":1673.48,"duration":6.15},{"text":"He -- he didn't admit to the number of -- of the drinks that he had -- that he -- that the bartender served him but he did admit that he had been drinking there all afternoon.","start":1673.48,"stop":1685.735,"duration":12.25}]},{"speakerName":"William J. Brennan, Jr.","textObjs":[{"text":"Did the jury draw any inferences of the -- driving from that --","start":1685.735,"stop":1689.08,"duration":3.35}]},{"speakerName":"H. Alva Brumfield","textObjs":[{"text":"Yes sir, under the influence of liquor, yes sir, that in itself.","start":1689.08,"stop":1692.233,"duration":3.15},{"text":"There's many in the -- instances where the negligence is -- is presumed.","start":1692.233,"stop":1696.477,"duration":4.24},{"text":"I'm making a left hand turn and -- and passing a car on a bridge is all -- all types of situations where presumptions can be drawn and inferences where a fact situation is produced.","start":1696.477,"stop":1708.152,"duration":11.67}]},{"speakerName":"Hugo L. Black","textObjs":[{"text":"What evidence was the connection of the facts the way they ran, I wonder if --","start":1708.152,"stop":1713.971,"duration":5.82}]},{"speakerName":"William J. Brennan, Jr.","textObjs":[{"text":"The -- the fact that the body, I'm looking at the photographs if I had them here, Your Honor could show, you see the body lying there in the direct line --","start":1713.971,"stop":1721.711,"duration":7.74}]},{"speakerName":"Hugo L. Black","textObjs":[{"text":"(Voice Overlap) -- did they show a straight line?","start":1721.711,"stop":1722.8,"duration":1.09}]},{"speakerName":"William J. Brennan, Jr.","textObjs":[{"text":"Straight line deviated from the asphalt onto the shoulder and then back on to the asphalt.","start":1722.8,"stop":1729.37,"duration":6.57}]},{"speakerName":"Hugo L. Black","textObjs":[{"text":"(Inaudible)","start":1729.37,"stop":1730.166,"duration":0.8}]},{"speakerName":"H. Alva Brumfield","textObjs":[{"text":"(Inaudible)","start":1730.166,"stop":1730.506,"duration":0.34},{"text":"Off of it, some about two of three feet off of the asphalt portion of the highway.","start":1730.506,"stop":1736.3,"duration":5.79}]},{"speakerName":"Byron R. White","textObjs":[{"text":"Is this a dirt (Inaudible)?","start":1736.3,"stop":1737.932,"duration":1.63}]},{"speakerName":"H. Alva Brumfield","textObjs":[{"text":"It's a grass, it was grass.","start":1737.932,"stop":1739.342,"duration":1.41}]},{"speakerName":"Byron R. White","textObjs":[{"text":"There was no footprint?","start":1739.342,"stop":1741.039,"duration":1.7}]},{"speakerName":"H. Alva Brumfield","textObjs":[{"text":"No, but the tire tracks are shown in the grass itself.","start":1741.039,"stop":1744.212,"duration":3.17},{"text":"The grass was rather high and they were still there, went -- in the next morning when the photograph of the body was taken as shown in these photographs, the -- the tire track.","start":1744.212,"stop":1753.695,"duration":9.48}]},{"speakerName":"Byron R. White","textObjs":[{"text":"Well, I take it, what the evidence shows is that the -- well, it seems to show that somebody was hit and if he was hit, he must have gone up on the hood.","start":1753.695,"stop":1763.324,"duration":9.63}]},{"speakerName":"H. Alva Brumfield","textObjs":[{"text":"He must have been.","start":1763.324,"stop":1764.18,"duration":0.86},{"text":"The right -- and you see it all fixed because he's walking on the right hand side of the road and the car is coming from his back and the right fender and the right headlight was what was damaged and the right portion of the hood.","start":1764.18,"stop":1777.171,"duration":12.99},{"text":"So when that body hit the fender and headlight hit the body, it slipped him apparently because when he went right on over the -- the -- there's a big dent in the hood near the windshield as the body was clipped -- clipped over.","start":1777.171,"stop":1792.218,"duration":15.05}]},{"speakerName":"Byron R. White","textObjs":[{"text":"So, he must -- then he drove off to the side then?","start":1792.218,"stop":1794.822,"duration":2.6}]},{"speakerName":"H. Alva Brumfield","textObjs":[{"text":"And then either clipped or just flipped all away over, of course you can't tell but the -- but with the body landing, it was right faced down and the tracks are right there.","start":1794.822,"stop":1803.989,"duration":9.17},{"text":"So when he flipped, he's riding the path.","start":1803.989,"stop":1806.551,"duration":2.56}]},{"speakerName":"Byron R. White","textObjs":[{"text":"(Inaudible)","start":1806.551,"stop":1808.182,"duration":1.63}]},{"speakerName":"H. Alva Brumfield","textObjs":[{"text":"He could very well have --","start":1808.182,"stop":1809.49,"duration":1.31}]},{"speakerName":"Byron R. White","textObjs":[{"text":"(Inaudible)","start":1809.49,"stop":1811.615,"duration":2.13}]},{"speakerName":"H. Alva Brumfield","textObjs":[{"text":"He couldn't have stayed there.","start":1811.615,"stop":1812.335,"duration":0.72},{"text":"It knocked him off to the end of the ditch but it -- but apparently it just -- they flipped him over and he landed right in the tracks and the pool of blood was there as one of the deputies who investigated was found right in the -- in the truck itself.","start":1812.335,"stop":1826.244,"duration":13.91}]},{"speakerName":"Hugo L. Black","textObjs":[{"text":"Was there any kind of paint on his clothes of any kind?","start":1826.244,"stop":1831.039,"duration":4.8}]},{"speakerName":"H. Alva Brumfield","textObjs":[{"text":"Mr. Justice Black, he had this overall zone with blue denim and the -- the officers who took the scrapings of it, that was in the dented part of the -- of the hood, took the scrapings off, he said there was a poor slack like -- like it was a fabric.","start":1831.039,"stop":1847.097,"duration":16.06},{"text":"And then -- and of course analysis of -- and a laboratory would have proved indefinite but his testimony was as an investigating officer was that it came from the blue denim of his overalls and I don't think there's any --","start":1847.097,"stop":1859.95,"duration":12.85}]},{"speakerName":"Hugo L. Black","textObjs":[{"text":"But what the --","start":1859.95,"stop":1861.25,"duration":1.3}]},{"speakerName":"H. Alva Brumfield","textObjs":[{"text":"-- question about that.","start":1861.25,"stop":1862.138,"duration":0.89}]},{"speakerName":"Tom C. Clark","textObjs":[{"text":"That was the part of this dispute.","start":1862.138,"stop":1864.195,"duration":2.06}]},{"speakerName":"H. Alva Brumfield","textObjs":[{"text":"And that was what was destroyed and we had the skulduggeries as Judge Reeves call it in the -- in the destruction of this evidence which brought all of this invalid but -- but I -- that -- this pinpoints to me the -- the greatness of a jury trial and -- and where the determination of the facts where you have sufficient evidence produced, where the circumstance, physical or by eyewitness to have that determinative facts, be a judge or jury to see these witnesses and hear them and not make a determination of fact from a cold record.","start":1864.195,"stop":1907.03,"duration":42.84},{"text":"Because it's -- it's just not the same and -- and just like Judge Wright said, when he denied the motion for a new trial in this case after the verdict came in from the jury, he says no one who sat through this case and heard these witnesses could come to no other conclusion but that what the jury did.","start":1907.03,"stop":1927.109,"duration":20.08},{"text":"And then when he came back down and after it was remanded with his mandate and after it went through these other depositions trying to find some evidence that had been destroyed by this someone -- one pointing to the other.","start":1927.109,"stop":1945.855,"duration":18.75},{"text":"Judge Wright made this statement and I -- I would like to read it for you because to me that -- even if he had tried this case without a jury, there had been no -- no question of what decision he would have rendered because here's what he said.","start":1945.855,"stop":1961.487,"duration":15.63},{"text":"There isn't any question in my mind that that there was a denial of justice in this case.","start":1961.487,"stop":1969.68,"duration":8.19},{"text":"There isn't any question in my mind either that Paris Theriot killed this man.","start":1969.68,"stop":1977.31,"duration":7.63},{"text":"Now, how can you have a miscarriage of justice in the state court before a jury and a judge and still have a miscarriage of justice in the Fifth Circuit Court of Appeal for the defendant.","start":1977.31,"stop":1996.665,"duration":19.36}]},{"speakerName":"Arthur J. Goldberg","textObjs":[{"text":"(Inaudible)","start":1996.665,"stop":2001.833,"duration":5.17}]},{"speakerName":"H. Alva Brumfield","textObjs":[{"text":"Had he changed his mind and he --","start":2001.833,"stop":2003.387,"duration":1.55}]},{"speakerName":"Arthur J. Goldberg","textObjs":[{"text":"(Inaudible)","start":2003.387,"stop":2005.532,"duration":2.14}]},{"speakerName":"H. Alva Brumfield","textObjs":[{"text":"Right judge and I -- I beg Judge Wright, has said, I -- he -- he was on the impression that -- that the mandate provided that -- that the plaintiff had defined additional evidence.","start":2005.532,"stop":2016.495,"duration":10.96},{"text":"And of course Judge Wisdom in his decision says that that's the only interpretation of it.","start":2016.495,"stop":2021.364,"duration":4.87},{"text":"But -- but if the case had been retried and resubmitted on the exact evidence, there was educed at the first trial, the decision would still have been the same.","start":2021.364,"stop":2030.926,"duration":9.56},{"text":"And that's the reason we are here now and asking this Court to reverse this case and render and that is restore the jury of verdict as there is no need for a new trial in this case.The evidence has been educed.","start":2030.926,"stop":2048.091,"duration":17.16},{"text":"Thank you very much.","start":2048.091,"stop":2048.775,"duration":0.68}]},{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"Yes.","start":2048.775,"stop":2049.62,"duration":0.84}]}]}],"decidedBy":"Warren Court","arguedOn":"Apr 22, 1964","petitioner":"Mercer","respondent":"Theriot","docket":"336","citation":"377US152(1964)","justiaLink":"https://supreme.justia.com/cases/federal/us/377/152","lowerCourt":"United States Court of Appeals for the Fifth Circuit","grantedOn":"","decidedOn":"May 4, 1964"}